  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>·\nPlanning daily and weekly work schedules and controlling the cost of projects.</p><p>·\nOrganize teams of foremen and labour to perform different tasks at different\nlocations.</p><p>·\nResource planning such as material, machinery, equipment and manpower for the\nproject.</p><p>· Liaise\nwith clients' supervisors on work matters.</p><p>· Conduct\ndaily toolbox meetings to educate and communicate with foreign labour.</p><p>· Sound\nknowledge of building codes and construction safety regulations.</p><p>· Working\nknowledge of construction tools and equipment.</p><p>·\nOutstanding leadership skills.</p><p>· Strong\nanalytical and problem-solving skills.</p><p>·\nExcellent organizational and communication skills.</p><p>·\nChecking of works done by Foremen and labour force to ensure that they are\ncorrect and of good quality.</p><p>·\nTroubleshoot problems on-site in order to ensure any delays are minimized and\nadditional costs reduced.<br />Job\nrequirements:</p><p>· Good\nInterpersonal and communication skills.</p><p>·\nIndependent, resourceful, diligent and a good team player.</p><p>· Able to\nlead workers to comply, fulfil project requirements, meeting schedules.</p><p>·\nExpected to perform hands-on duties with acquired skills and knowledge.</p><p>·\nExperience in troubleshooting, maintaining and repair for common equipment on\nthe construction site.</p><p>· Working\nirregular hours and night shifts is common</p><p>. Minimum\n10-year experience at construction sector as a safety personnel.</p><p>.\nPossesses Building Construction Supervisors Safety Course (BCSS) and\nWork-At-Height (WAH)</p><p>. Have\nknowledge in using Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</p><p>. Willing\nto work night shift and split shift or rotating shift, if required.</p><p>. Willing\nto work on public holiday or rotating shift</p><p>. Possess\ngood communication skills and can-do attitude</p>",
